      • broadcastDedupParams

        public void broadcastDedupParams(org.apache.spark.SparkContext cxt)
        Broadcasts dedupParams and replaces the local reference with a reference to the broadcasted variable. Broadcasted variables are deserialized once per executor instead of once per task. Broadcasting can reduce execution time significantly for jobs with a large number of partitions.
